15/08/2003
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Police on Thursday (14 August) charged 11 teenagers with the highly publicised beatings of foreigners over the past two weeks. The son of an Egyptian embassy official and an Austrian family of Pakistani descent were the targets of the attacks, all of which occurred in Zagreb. The suspects, aged 16 to 20, admitted to carrying out the attacks under the influence of alcohol. (AFP - 14/08/03)
